Except for a roof that is made up of a concrete slab and has a height of more than 2 m, measured between the average ground level and the highest part of the seal membrane, a vegetated roof shall meet the following standards: 1. consist of the following components installed above a traditional roof assembly: (a) vegetation; (b) a substrate or growth medium; (c) a filter layer; (d) a drainage system; (e) a water retention system or layer;
(f) a barrier that prevents the roots from piercing the roof seal membrane and that complies with ANSI/GRHC/SPRI VR-1 2011 "Procedure for investigating resistance to root penetration on vegetative roofs" attached to Annex D to these Regulations; 2° not to be fitted on a roof with shingles or tiles; 3° subject to paragraph 4o, to be fitted on an incombustible building; 4° to be type 1 when fitted on a fuel building;
5° form a fire-resistant separation of a fire-resistant level equal to that required by the Code, but not less than 45 minutes, when the fire-resistant separation is made above the roof of a building that is of a fuel-built construction and is not protected by sprinklers; 6° include openings in the roof deck to allow the gas and smoke to be removed when the fire-resistant opening is above a roof vacuum that is of a fuel-built construction and is not protected by sprinklers; these openings shall: (a) have a minimum surface area of 0.7 m2 and no dimension less than 760 mm; (b) be protected from weather;
(c) be fitted with a lid which can be easily removed without the use of a special tool; (d) be easily accessible and properly identified; (e) be provided for an opening per vacuum compartment under roof referred to in paragraph 7o; and 7° in the case where a vacuum under a fuel-built roof is not protected by sprinklers and has an area of more than 300 m2, be divided into compartments of which individual is not more than 300 m2. These compartments shall be insulated from each other by fire-stops in accordance with paragraph 1 of Article 3.1.11.7 of Division B of the Code.
However, such openings are not required when the following characteristics are met: (a) the building has a building area of not more than 300 m2; (b) the vegetated roof occupies not more than 50% of the total surface of a roof or that of a section of roof when isolated from the rest of the roof; and (b) the 8° area, subject to paragraph 9o, includes suitable devices, designed and positioned to erode components when fitted on an inclined roof which is more than 10 degrees (17%) in relation to the horizontal;
to prevent 9° from incorporating suitable devices, designed and positioned to prevent erosion of components and their slipping when fitted on an inclined roof which is more than 14 degrees (25 per cent) from the horizontal; 10° to be fitted on a roof designed, in accordance with the requirements of Part 4 of Division B of the Code and those of the standards mentioned in this sub-section; 11° to be subject to paragraphs 12o and 13o, in addition to the loads and overloads mentioned in section 4.1.
The calculation of Division B of the Code shall also take into account the loads associated with a plant-based roof in full saturation, which are determined in accordance with ASTM E2397-11 "Standard practice for determination of dead loads and live loads associated with vegetable (green) roof systems" and ASTM E2399-11 "Standard test method for maximum media density for dead load analysis of vegetable (green) roof systems" attached to Annex E to this Regulation;
12° where the load associated with the saturated growth substrate cannot be determined according to the standards mentioned in paragraph 11o, it shall be calculated on the basis of a density of 2,000 kg/m3 (or 125 pounds/ft3); 13° calculations of the structural resistance of the roof shall also take into account: (a) overloads due to other materials and equipment intended for a vegetated roof; (b) overloads due to use when the vegetated roof is accessible in accordance with sub-section 4.1.8. of Division B of the Code;
14° be designed to withstand the wind-induced uplift and erosion effects, in accordance with the rules of art, in particular those described in ANSI/SPRI RP-14 "Wind Design Standard for Vegetative Roofing Systems" attached to Annex F to these Regulations; 15° the calculations referred to in paragraphs 13 and 14o shall be made by a person competent in this matter; 16° the hydraulic load from the roof water shall be calculated in accordance with Chapter III, Plumbing, of the Code, assuming that the vegetated roof is fully saturated with water before the 15 minute precipitation, as determined by the climatic data referred to in section 1.1.3.
Division B of the Code; 17° drainage shall be adequately under the growth substrate layer and shall not permit any infiltration of this substrate or any other material into roof swallows; 18° within a vegetated roof basin or a vegetated roof section, the drains shall not be of a controlled flow type defined in Chapter III, Plumbing, of the Code; 19° the drainage system shall be selected according to ASTM E2398- 11 "Standard Test Method for Water Capture and Media Retention of Geo- composite Drain Layers for Green Roof Systems" attached to Appendix G to these Regulations;
20° where parapets are provided on the edge of a roof, analyses and calculations shall be made in accordance with the requirements of section 4.1.6.4 of Division B of the Code, to ensure that the structural capacity of the roof can withstand the load of accumulated rainwater, should the roof swallows be blocked; 21° individual area of a vegetated roof or a section of a green roof shall not exceed: (a) 300 m2 when the building is of combustible construction; (b) 900 m2 when the building is of non-combustible construction; 22° no dimension of a vegetated roof or a section of a vegetated roof shall be greater than 30 m;
23° where the building has a type 2 green roof or a building area greater than 300 m2 and a type 1 green roof, a vegetation-free area of (a) not less than 0.5 m around the roof drains, measured from the centre of the swallowing site; (b) not less than 0.5 m around a vegetated roof or a vegetated roof section; (c) not less than 0.5 m between a vegetated roof and any equipment on the roof, including plumbing and ventilation equipment, pipes, pipes, antennas and expansion joints; (d) not less than 1 m between 2 contiguous sections of vegetated roof defined in paragraphs 21o or 22o;
(e) at least 1.2 m between a vegetated roof and: (i) a roof-out construction; (ii) the axis of a fire-proof wall; (iii) an external wall belonging to the same building; (iv) a property boundary, except that which is bordered by a public road; (v) lanterns, pergolas, terraces; 24° where the building has a building area of not more than 300 m2 and has a type 1 green roof, a vegetation-free area of not less than 0.35 m wide around a roof-outer measured from the centre of the swallow; (b) at least 0.5 m around a vegetated roof or a vegetated roof section;
(c) not less than 0.3 m between a vegetated roof and any equipment on the roof, including plumbing and ventilation equipment, pipes, ducts, antennas, expansion joints and lanterns; (d) not less than 0.5 m between a vegetated roof and an off-roof construction; 25° a zone free of vegetation required shall be isolated from the adjacent section of the vegetated roof by a border whose upper part must be at least the same level as the top of the growing substrate and whose presence does not affect the drainage of the roof; 26° the areas free of vegetation required shall be covered with non-combustible materials;
27° the top of a vegetation-free area required around a swallow shall be made of non-combustible materials that facilitate drainage; 28° the width of vegetation-free areas may be reduced to 0.5 m where the elements referred to in subparagraphs (i), (ii), and (v) of subparagraph (e) of paragraph 23o are non-combustible or are covered by non-combustible materials; 29° when a green roof is accessible, it shall be considered to be used within the meaning of the Code. A green roof shall be considered accessible where persons may have access to it for functions other than maintenance;
30° a green roof shall be fitted with an integrated irrigation system or at least one watering tap, installed on the roof or at any other suitable location; 31° before the installation of a green roof, the owner shall carry out or have carried out, at his own expense, a leakproof test according to one of the methods recognized by the industry; This article does not apply to roofs or roofing parts intended for growing vegetation in greenhouses, bins or pots. SUB-SECTION II COMBUSTIBLE WELLS – HERITAGE

A storage cabinet installed on a balcony may be treated as a projection under the following conditions: 1° its area shall be not more than 2.5 m2; 2° the part of the outer wall of the building to which it is attached shall have the same composition as that of the whole wall; 3° except for a building which has not more than 2 units, any part of the floor and roof within 1.2 m of a boundary of ownership or axis of a fire-resistant wall shall be of uncombustible construction;
4° the inner side of the wall adjacent to or within 1.2 m from a boundary of ownership not bordering a highway or the axis of a firewall shall be covered by non-combustible material ensuring a fire resistance of at least 1 hour; 5° the outer side of the wall adjacent to or within 1.2 m from a boundary of ownership not bordering a highway or the axis of a firewall shall be covered by non-combustible material ensuring fire resistance of at least 1 hour and an uncombustible weather-resistant trim;
6° when 2 storage cabinets are superimposed, the lower part of the floor-ceiling assembly separating them shall be covered with non-combustible material ensuring fire resistance of at least 1 hour. SUB-DIVISION III CONCEPT OF THE AIRES AND SPACE IN A HEAT

Article 28 of the Regulations is amended by: 1. the first paragraph of the words "n-is not" is replaced by the words "may not be"; 2. the second paragraph of the first paragraph of the following paragraph is replaced by the following: "6° each suite with a mezzanine shall be isolated from the rest of the building by a fire-stop separation of at least 1 hour"; 3. the second paragraph shall be replaced by the following: "However, for the purposes of subsections 9.9.9. and 9.10.18. of Division B of the Code, the mezzanines referred to in the first subparagraph shall constitute a floor"; 4. the third paragraph of the first paragraph shall be replaced by the words "consisting of";
5° the last paragraph shall be replaced by the following: "Despite paragraph 2 of section 9.10.18.2. of Division B of the Code, a fire alarm system shall be required in a dwelling which has mezzanine referred to in the first paragraph where the building has more than 3 floor levels other than those below the first floor and contains more than 4 units. Where such a fire alarm system is required, in addition to the components required by the Code, a heat detector allowing both the detection of a maximum fixed temperature and the rise of temperature shall be installed in each dwelling and in each room not forming part of a dwelling.
"

Section 34 of these Regulations is amended by: 1. the replacement in paragraph 5 of the second subparagraph of paragraph 5 of the second subparagraph of the words "and the telephone number" by the words ", the telephone number and the email address"; 2. the replacement in subparagraph 6(b) of the second subparagraph of the words "and the cut" by the words ", cut and detail"; 3. the addition after subparagraph 6(b) of the second subparagraph of paragraph 6(b) of the following subparagraph: "(c) subparagraph (a) does not apply to the following work: (i) the replacement of doors and windows without modification of their dimensions; (ii) the replacement of a roof covering; and (iii) the fitting of a green roof;
(iv) any other work which is not considered to be a transformation within the meaning of the Code."; 4. the replacement of the words "plan d'implantation" in subparagraph 7(a) of the second subparagraph by the words "plan d'implantation"; 5. the replacement of subparagraph 7(b) of the second subparagraph by the following: "(b) in the case of an expansion of an existing building: (i) a plan d'implantation project containing the same information as required in paragraph 7(b) of the second subparagraph of this article when necessary to enable the project to be verified as to whether it complies with the applicable municipal regulations;
(ii) a certificate of location;"; 6° the replacement of paragraph 9° of the second subparagraph by the following: "9° in the case of an application for a licence by an agent, be accompanied by a power of attorney from the owner of the building. In the case of a building held in a divided condominium, the applicant or his agent shall provide the authorization of the condominium union for any work to be performed in a common part."; 7° the addition after paragraph 4° of the third subparagraph of the following paragraph:
"5° in the case of the development of a vegetated roof referred to in the first paragraph of the first paragraph of section 27.4, be accompanied by the following documents: (a) the vegetated roof sheet duly completed and signed by the designer in respect of structural resistance, wind-induced lifting effects and roof-bearing capacity when parapets are required; and (b) the roof structure plans and elements supporting it."
